<leg xml:space="preserve" billnum="SB0062" sponsor="Lincoln Fillmore" designation="SB" otherSponsor="Matt MacPherson" otherHouse="House" subNumber="02" subSponsor="Lincoln Fillmore" sess="2026GS" fileno="2026FL0678" date="2/11/2026 15:02:860" printDate="02-23 17:26" subVer="2" minVer="0" office="LEGISLATIVE GENERAL COUNSEL" actionDate="" impact="code"><info><nextbuid>31</nextbuid><aminfo anum="0" effdate="07/01/2027"><seclist><sect action="A" src="code" buid="1" uid="C53F-2-S302_2027070120270701" fromuid="C53F-2-S302_2024031320240501" sort="53F02 03020020270701" mtype="section" effdate="07/01/2027">53F-2-302</sect><sect action="E" src="code" buid="23" uid="C53F-2-S307.5_2027070120270701" sort="53F02 03070520270701" mtype="section" effdate="07/01/2027">53F-2-307.5</sect><sect src="uncod" untype="effdate" buid="30" uid="EF0000" sort="UZEFF" mtype="uncod" effdate="07/01/2027"/></seclist></aminfo></info><tbox><sinfo><nextpairid>0</nextpairid></sinfo><st numlevel="1" lineno="1" slineno="0-1">School Funding Amendments</st><sessionhead>2026 GENERAL SESSION</sessionhead><statehead>STATE OF UTAH</statehead><sponsorhead>Chief Sponsor: Lincoln Fillmore</sponsorhead><otherSponsorhead>House Sponsor: Matt MacPherson</otherSponsorhead></tbox><lt numlevel="1" lineno="2" slineno="0-2"><lthead lineno="3">LONG TITLE</lthead><gdhead lineno="4">General Description:</gdhead><gd numlevel="1" lineno="5" slineno="0-5">This bill modifies provisions regarding weighted pupil units.</gd><hphead lineno="6">Highlighted Provisions:</hphead><hp numlevel="1" lineno="7" slineno="0-7">This bill:<hl numlevel="1" lineno="8" slineno="0-8" level="1">modifies the formula to determine a school district's weighted pupil units by:<hl numlevel="1" lineno="9" slineno="0-9" level="2">repealing an exclusion for self-contained classes for children with a disability; and</hl><hl numlevel="1" lineno="10" slineno="0-10" level="2">accounting for positive or negative growth based on the current school year's student <ln numlevel="1" lineno="11" slineno="0-11"/>count; and</hl></hl><hl numlevel="1" lineno="12" slineno="0-12" level="1">reallocates savings from enrollment decline to special education self-contained weighted <ln numlevel="1" lineno="13" slineno="0-13"/>pupil units and weighted pupil units for students who are at-risk;</hl><hl numlevel="1" lineno="14" slineno="0-14" level="1">creates special education self-contained weighted pupil units; and</hl><hl numlevel="1" lineno="15" slineno="0-15" level="1">makes technical and conforming changes.</hl></hp><moni numlevel="1" lineno="16" slineno="0-16" display="none">Money Appropriated in this Bill:</moni><moniNone lineno="17">None</moniNone><oc numlevel="1" lineno="18" slineno="0-18">Other Special Clauses:<ocl type="effdate" sort="2" numlevel="1" lineno="19" slineno="0-19">This bill provides a special effective date.</ocl></oc><sa numlevel="1" lineno="20" slineno="0-20">Utah Code Sections Affected:<saamd numlevel="1" lineno="21" slineno="0-21"><snhead>AMENDS:</snhead><sn num="53F-2-302" src="code" uid="C53F-2-S302_2027070120270701" buid="1" sort="53F02 03020020270701" numlevel="1" lineno="22" slineno="0-22"><bold>53F-2-302</bold>, as last amended by Laws of Utah 2024, Chapter 124</sn></saamd><saent numlevel="1" lineno="23" slineno="0-23"><snhead>ENACTS:</snhead><sn num="53F-2-307.5" src="code" uid="C53F-2-S307.5_2027070120270701" buid="23" sort="53F02 03070520270701" numlevel="1" lineno="24" slineno="0-24"><bold>53F-2-307.5</bold>, Utah Code Annotated 1953</sn></saent></sa></lt><enacthead lineno="25"/><enact numlevel="1" lineno="26" slineno="0-26">Be it enacted by the Legislature of the state of Utah:</enact><bdy><bsec buid="1" num="53F-2-302" type="amend" src="code" uid="C53F-2-S302_2027070120270701" sort="53F02 03020020270701" numlevel="1" lineno="27" slineno="1-1" sn="1"><section number="53F-2-302" numlevel="1" lineno="28" slineno="1-2" type="amend"><secline lineno="27">Section 1. Section <bold>53F-2-302</bold> is amended to read:</secline><catline lineno="28"><bold>53F-2-302<parens/>. Determination of weighted pupil units.</bold></catline><subsection ssid="1-null-1" dnum="1-o" numlevel="1" lineno="29" slineno="1-3" level="1" placement="noreturn"><display>(1)</display>The number of weighted pupil units in the Minimum School Program for each year is <ln numlevel="1" lineno="30" slineno="1-4"/>the total of the units for each school district and, subject to Subsection <xref depth="4" refnumber="53F-2-302(5)">(5)</xref>, charter <ln numlevel="1" lineno="31" slineno="1-5"/>school, determined in accordance with this section.</subsection><subsection ssid="1-null-2" dnum="2-o" numlevel="1" lineno="32" slineno="1-6" level="1"><display>(2)</display>The number of weighted pupil units is computed by adding the average daily <ln numlevel="1" lineno="33" slineno="1-7"/>membership of all pupils of the LEA attending schools<amendoutstart style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="erase" pairid="38" groupid="34" style="2" owner="ahaskell" level="1" deltag="both">, other than self-contained <ln numlevel="1" lineno="34" slineno="1-8"/>classes for children with a disability</amend><amendoutend style="2"/>.</subsection><subsection ssid="1-null-3" dnum="3-o" numlevel="1" lineno="35" slineno="1-9" level="1" space="false"><display>(3)</display><subsection ssid="1-null-4" dnum="a-o" level="2" placement="sameline"><display>(a)</display>Except as provided in Subsection <xref depth="4" refnumber="53F-2-302(3)(b)">(3)(b)</xref>, for a fiscal year beginning on or after <ln numlevel="1" lineno="36" slineno="1-10"/>July 1, 2023, the number of weighted pupil units for kindergarten students shall be <ln numlevel="1" lineno="37" slineno="1-11"/>computed by adding the average daily membership of all pupils of the LEA enrolled <ln numlevel="1" lineno="38" slineno="1-12"/>in kindergarten.</subsection><subsection ssid="1-null-5" dnum="b-o" numlevel="1" lineno="39" slineno="1-13" level="2"><display>(b)</display>The number of weighted pupil units is computed by multiplying the average daily <ln numlevel="1" lineno="40" slineno="1-14"/>membership for the number of students who are enrolled in kindergarten for less than <ln numlevel="1" lineno="41" slineno="1-15"/>the equivalent length of the schedule for grades 1 through 3, based on the October 1 <ln numlevel="1" lineno="42" slineno="1-16"/>data described in Section <xref depth="3" refnumber="53F-2-302">53F-2-302</xref>, by .55.</subsection></subsection><subsection ssid="1-null-6" dnum="4-o" numlevel="1" lineno="43" slineno="1-17" level="1" space="false"><display>(4)</display><subsection ssid="1-null-7" dnum="a-o" level="2" placement="sameline"><display>(a)</display>The state board shall <amendoutstart style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="erase" pairid="45" groupid="40" style="2" owner="ahaskell" level="1" deltag="both">use prior year plus growth to determine average daily <ln numlevel="1" lineno="44" slineno="1-18"/>membership in distributing</amend><amendoutend style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="44" groupid="39" style="1" owner="ahaskell" level="1" amendtag="both" space="true">distribute</amend> money under the Minimum School Program <ln numlevel="1" lineno="45" slineno="1-19"/>where the distribution is based on kindergarten through grade 12 ADMs <amendoutstart style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="erase" pairid="46" groupid="41" style="2" owner="ahaskell" level="1" deltag="both">or weighted <ln numlevel="1" lineno="46" slineno="1-20"/>pupil units.</amend><amendoutend style="2"/><subsection ssid="1-null-8" dnum="b-o:_-i" numlevel="1" lineno="47" slineno="1-21" ea="erase" anum="0" owner="ahaskell" style="2" level="2" tab="1"><display><amendoutstart style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="erase" pairid="1007" style="2" owner="o" level="1" deltag="start">(b)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="erase" pairid="47" groupid="42" style="2" owner="ahaskell" level="1" deltag="end">Under prior year plus growth, kindergarten through grade 12 average daily <ln numlevel="1" lineno="48" slineno="1-22"/>membership for the current year is </amend><amendoutend style="2"/>based on the actual kindergarten through grade <ln numlevel="1" lineno="49" slineno="1-23"/>12 average daily membership for the previous year plus an estimated percentage <ln numlevel="1" lineno="50" slineno="1-24"/>growth factor.</subsection></subsection><subsection ssid="1-null-9" dnum="c-o:b-i" numlevel="1" lineno="51" slineno="1-25" level="2"><display><amendoutstart style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="erase" pairid="1008" style="2" owner="o" level="1" deltag="both">(c)</amend><amendoutend style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1009" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="both" space="true">(b)</amend></display>The growth factor is the percentage increase <amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="26" groupid="24" style="1" owner="ahaskell" level="1" amendtag="both">or decrease </amend>in total <amendoutstart style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="erase" pairid="59" groupid="51" style="2" owner="ahaskell" level="1" deltag="both">average daily <ln numlevel="1" lineno="52" slineno="1-26"/>membership</amend><amendoutend style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="56" groupid="48" style="1" owner="ahaskell" level="1" amendtag="both" space="true">student count</amend> on the first school day of October in the current year as <ln numlevel="1" lineno="53" slineno="1-27"/>compared to the total <amendoutstart style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="erase" pairid="60" groupid="52" style="2" owner="ahaskell" level="1" deltag="both">average daily membership</amend><amendoutend style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="57" groupid="49" style="1" owner="ahaskell" level="1" amendtag="both" space="true">student count</amend> on the first school <ln numlevel="1" lineno="54" slineno="1-28"/>day of October of the previous year.</subsection><subsection ssid="1-null-10" dnum="d-o:_-i" numlevel="1" lineno="55" slineno="1-29" ea="erase" anum="0" owner="ahaskell" style="2" level="2"><display><amendoutstart style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="erase" pairid="1009" style="2" owner="o" level="1" deltag="start">(d)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="erase" pairid="61" groupid="53" style="2" owner="ahaskell" level="1" deltag="end">If the calculations described in Subsections (4)(a) through (c) show a loss in <ln numlevel="1" lineno="56" slineno="1-30"/>enrollment for an LEA due to factors beyond the LEA's control, the state board may <ln numlevel="1" lineno="57" slineno="1-31"/>allow a percentage increase in units for the LEA to account for the loss.</amend><amendoutend style="2"/></subsection></subsection><subsection ssid="1-null-11" dnum="5-o" numlevel="1" lineno="58" slineno="1-32" level="1"><display>(5)</display>In distributing funds to charter schools under this section, charter school pupils shall be <ln numlevel="1" lineno="59" slineno="1-33"/>weighted, where applicable, as follows:<subsection ssid="1-null-12" dnum="a-o" numlevel="1" lineno="60" slineno="1-34" level="2"><display>(a)</display>except as provided in Subsection <xref depth="4" refnumber="53F-2-302(3)(b)">(3)(b)</xref>, .9 for pupils in kindergarten through grade 6;</subsection><subsection ssid="1-null-13" dnum="b-o" numlevel="1" lineno="61" slineno="1-35" level="2"><display>(b)</display>.99 for pupils in grades 7 through 8; and</subsection><subsection ssid="1-null-14" dnum="c-o" numlevel="1" lineno="62" slineno="1-36" level="2"><display>(c)</display>1.2 for pupils in grades 9 through 12.</subsection></subsection><subsection ssid="1-17" dnum="_-o:6-i" numlevel="1" lineno="63" slineno="1-37" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="ahaskell" style="1" level="1"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1014" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(6)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="42" groupid="37" style="1" owner="ahaskell" level="1" amendtag="end">In preparation of public education budgets, the Executive Appropriations Committee <ln numlevel="1" lineno="64" slineno="1-38"/>shall reallocate any savings from enrollment decline under Subsection <xref depth="4" refnumber="53F-2-302(4)">(4)</xref>:</amend><subsection ssid="1-18" dnum="_-o:a-i" numlevel="1" lineno="65" slineno="1-39" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="ahaskell" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1015" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(a)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="67" groupid="57" style="1" owner="ahaskell" level="1" amendtag="end"><marker pairid="62"/>for self-contained special education weighted pupil units under Section <xref depth="3" refnumber="53F-2-307.5">53F-2-307.5</xref>; <ln numlevel="1" lineno="66" slineno="1-40"/>and</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="1-19" dnum="_-o:b-i" numlevel="1" lineno="67" slineno="1-41" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="ahaskell" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1016" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(b)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="72" groupid="61" style="1" owner="ahaskell" level="1" amendtag="end">the remainder, after the amount described in Subsection <xref depth="4" refnumber="53F-2-302(6)(a)">(6)(a)</xref>, for weighted pupil <ln numlevel="1" lineno="68" slineno="1-42"/>units for students who are at-risk described in Section <xref depth="3" refnumber="53F-2-314">53F-2-314</xref>.</amend></subsection></subsection></section></bsec><bsec buid="23" num="53F-2-307.5" type="enact" src="code" uid="C53F-2-S307.5_2027070120270701" sort="53F02 03070520270701" numlevel="1" lineno="69" slineno="2-1" sn="2"><section numlevel="1" lineno="70" slineno="2-2" number="53F-2-307.5" type="enact"><secline lineno="69">Section 2. Section <bold>53F-2-307.5</bold> is enacted to read:</secline><catline lineno="70"><bold>53F-2-307.5<parens/>. Self-contained special education weighted pupil units.</bold></catline><subsection ssid="23-2" dnum="_-o:1-i" numlevel="1" lineno="71" slineno="2-3" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="ahaskell" style="1" level="1" placement="noreturn"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1017" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(1)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="8" groupid="6" style="1" owner="ahaskell" level="1" amendtag="end">As used in this section:</amend><subsection ssid="23-6" dnum="_-o:a-i" numlevel="1" lineno="72" slineno="2-4" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="ahaskell" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1018" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(a)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="20" groupid="14" style="1" owner="ahaskell" level="1" amendtag="end">"LEA" means:</amend><subsection ssid="23-7" dnum="_-o:i-i" numlevel="1" lineno="73" slineno="2-5" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="ahaskell" style="1" level="3"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1019" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(i)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="23" groupid="16" style="1" owner="ahaskell" level="1" amendtag="end">a school district; or</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="23-8" dnum="_-o:ii-i" numlevel="1" lineno="74" slineno="2-6" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="ahaskell" style="1" level="3"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1020" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(ii)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="26" groupid="18" style="1" owner="ahaskell" level="1" amendtag="end">a charter school.</amend></subsection></subsection><subsection ssid="23-53" dnum="_-o:b-i" numlevel="1" lineno="75" slineno="2-7" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="ahaskell" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1021" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(b)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="155" groupid="104" style="1" owner="ahaskell" level="1" amendtag="end">"Self-contained special education weighted pupil unit" means a weighted pupil unit <ln numlevel="1" lineno="76" slineno="2-8"/>for students who receive 180 minutes or more per day of specialized instruction in <ln numlevel="1" lineno="77" slineno="2-9"/>accordance with the student's IEP.</amend></subsection></subsection><subsection ssid="23-13" dnum="_-o:2-i" numlevel="1" lineno="78" slineno="2-10" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="ahaskell" style="1" level="1"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1022" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(2)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="44" groupid="30" style="1" owner="ahaskell" level="1" amendtag="end">A self-contained special education weighted pupil unit is equal to one pupil in average <ln numlevel="1" lineno="79" slineno="2-11"/>daily membership who receives 180 minutes or more per day of specialized instruction <ln numlevel="1" lineno="80" slineno="2-12"/>in accordance with the student's IEP.</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="23-19" dnum="_-o:3-i" numlevel="1" lineno="81" slineno="2-13" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="ahaskell" style="1" level="1" space="false"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1023" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(3)</amend></display><subsection ssid="23-56" dnum="_-o:a-i" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="ahaskell" style="1" level="2" placement="sameline"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1024" style="1" owner="i" level="1">(a)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="180" groupid="122" style="1" owner="ahaskell" level="1" amendtag="end">An LEA:</amend><subsection ssid="23-59" dnum="_-o:i-i" numlevel="1" lineno="82" slineno="2-14" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="ahaskell" style="1" level="3" tab="1"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1025" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(i)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="185" groupid="126" style="1" owner="ahaskell" level="1" amendtag="end">shall use self-contained special education classroom funding under this section to <ln numlevel="1" lineno="83" slineno="2-15"/>pay the costs of providing a self-contained special education classroom;</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="23-20" dnum="_-o:ii-i" numlevel="1" lineno="84" slineno="2-16" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="ahaskell" style="1" level="3" tab="1"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1026" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(ii)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="62" groupid="42" style="1" owner="ahaskell" level="1" amendtag="end">may use self-contained special education weighted pupil units to supplement <ln numlevel="1" lineno="85" slineno="2-17"/>other state funds, local funds, or federal funds; and</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="23-21" dnum="_-o:iii-i" numlevel="1" lineno="86" slineno="2-18" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="ahaskell" style="1" level="3" tab="1"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1027" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(iii)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="65" groupid="44" style="1" owner="ahaskell" level="1" amendtag="end">may not use self-contained special education weighted pupil units to supplant <ln numlevel="1" lineno="87" slineno="2-19"/>other state funds, local funds, or federal funds.</amend></subsection></subsection><subsection ssid="23-22" dnum="_-o:b-i" numlevel="1" lineno="88" slineno="2-20" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="ahaskell" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1028" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(b)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="68" groupid="46" style="1" owner="ahaskell" level="1" amendtag="end">Notwithstanding Subsection <xref depth="4" refnumber="53F-2-307.5(3)(a)">(3)(a)</xref>, an LEA may expend self-contained special <ln numlevel="1" lineno="89" slineno="2-21"/>education classroom funding for constructing facilities or altering existing facilities <ln numlevel="1" lineno="90" slineno="2-22"/>in accordance with Subsection <xref depth="4" refnumber="53F-2-307(4)">53F-2-307(4)</xref>.</amend></subsection></subsection><subsection ssid="23-33" dnum="_-o:4-i" numlevel="1" lineno="91" slineno="2-23" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="ahaskell" style="1" level="1" space="false"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1029" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(4)</amend></display><subsection ssid="23-34" dnum="_-o:a-i" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="ahaskell" style="1" level="2" placement="sameline"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1030" style="1" owner="i" level="1">(a)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="104" groupid="70" style="1" owner="ahaskell" level="1" amendtag="end">The state board shall allocate money appropriated to the state board for <ln numlevel="1" lineno="92" slineno="2-24"/>self-contained special education weighted pupil units based on an LEA's number of <ln numlevel="1" lineno="93" slineno="2-25"/>students with a disability in a self-contained special education classroom in <ln numlevel="1" lineno="94" slineno="2-26"/>accordance with this Subsection <xref depth="4" refnumber="53F-2-307.5(4)">(4)</xref>.</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="23-60" dnum="_-o:b-i" numlevel="1" lineno="95" slineno="2-27" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="ahaskell" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1031" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(b)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="190" groupid="130" style="1" owner="ahaskell" level="1" amendtag="end">The state board shall use an LEA's average number of self-contained special <ln numlevel="1" lineno="96" slineno="2-28"/>education weighted pupil units determined by the prior year's average daily <ln numlevel="1" lineno="97" slineno="2-29"/>membership plus growth.</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="23-62" dnum="_-o:c-i" numlevel="1" lineno="98" slineno="2-30" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="ahaskell" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1032" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(c)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="199" groupid="136" style="1" owner="ahaskell" level="1" amendtag="end">The growth factor described in Subsection <xref depth="4" refnumber="53F-2-307.5(4)(b)">(4)(b)</xref> is the percentage change in total <ln numlevel="1" lineno="99" slineno="2-31"/>enrollment of students in a self-contained special education classroom on the first <ln numlevel="1" lineno="100" slineno="2-32"/>school day of October in the current school year as compared to the total enrollment <ln numlevel="1" lineno="101" slineno="2-33"/>of students in a self-contained special education classroom on the first school day of <ln numlevel="1" lineno="102" slineno="2-34"/>October in the previous school year.</amend></subsection></subsection><subsection ssid="23-49" dnum="_-o:5-i" numlevel="1" lineno="103" slineno="2-35" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="ahaskell" style="1" level="1"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1033" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(5)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="149" groupid="100" style="1" owner="ahaskell" level="1" amendtag="end">If money appropriated under this chapter for programs for self-contained special <ln numlevel="1" lineno="104" slineno="2-36"/>education weighted pupil units does not meet the costs of LEAs for those programs, <ln numlevel="1" lineno="105" slineno="2-37"/>each LEA shall first receive the amount generated for each student with a disability <ln numlevel="1" lineno="106" slineno="2-38"/>under the basic program.</amend></subsection></section></bsec><bsec buid="30" type="uncod" untype="effdate" src="uncod" uid="EF0000" sort="UZEFF" langlock="true" numlevel="1" lineno="107" slineno="3-1" sn="3"><section type="uncod" untype="effdate" display="false" src="uncod"><secline lineno="107">Section 3.  <bold>Effective Date.</bold></secline><sectionText lineno="108"><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1" groupid="1" style="1" owner="ahaskell" level="1" amendtag="both">This bill takes effect on <effdate uid="code" date="7/1/2027">July 1, 2027</effdate>.</amend></sectionText></section></bsec></bdy><foot><rev><tm>2-11-26 3:42 PM</tm></rev></foot></leg>